  "response_text": "A white carpet sample is held upright in a clamp against a green wall. A woman’s hand steadies the left edge, and a pinkish circular stain appears near the center. Black on-screen text labels it “Red Wine.” The woman, seen partly from behind, has dark hair and wears a black top; only her profile and arm are visible at first.\n\nThe view widens to reveal a staged testing area that resembles an indoor range or lab, with green walls, metal posts, overhead strip lighting, and carpet samples hanging from clamps. The dark-haired woman in black stands behind a table at the center. She wears clear safety glasses and large black ear protectors. To the right, a blonde woman in a white outfit stands with her arms crossed, also wearing safety glasses and ear protectors, watching calmly. A blue aerosol can sits on the table near the dark-haired woman.\n\nThe dark-haired woman extends her arm straight out and sprays the blue aerosol can toward the stained carpet, holding it like a tool aimed at a target. A pale stream sprays from the nozzle across the space toward the hanging carpet sample. The can’s label is partly visible and includes large white lettering for a spot cleaner. Her expression is serious and focused. The carpet sample is shown again hanging in the clamp; the stain area looks muted but still faintly marked.\n\nThe blonde woman then steps forward in the same testing area, wearing a white blouse and light trousers. She reaches out with both hands and presents a different product close to the viewer: Woolite Oxy Deep 2X. The package looks like two silver aerosol cylinders joined side by side in a red-and-blue holder, with a red cap and a handle-like blue piece. The label is bold, with “Woolite” above large white “OXY DEEP” text and “2X” near the bottom. She holds it steadily, almost like a double-barreled device, with a confident, slight smile.\n\nA comparison appears on the green wall: two white carpet samples hang side by side from black clamps. 